snippet.title: (PS1) D Intro
snippet.description:
http://theplaygamer.blogspot.com/2011/05/theplaygamer3-d.html

D (Dの食卓 Dī no Shokutaku?) is a puzzle-oriented survival horror adventure game released in 1995 by WARP. The first entry in the D series and one of the first games released by the company, it dealt with taboo content such as violence and cannibalism, featured 3D CGI full-motion video and a first-person perspective, and introduced the star of Enemy Zero and D2, Laura.
